Chet,<br><br>
Let's put it this way: there are many ways to prove one's manhood.<br><br>
I would tell a young man of today who may never have to go to war that to &quot;prove himself&quot;, he should be a man that takes care of his family. <br><br>
Be a real father and husband, and when mom and dad become infirm in their winter years - be a good son.<br><br>
It is easy to get caught up in hero stuff - especially when we are frequenting war related sites. But the real men are out there every single day taking care of business and working hard. That is where the emphasis should lie.<br><br>
Vietnam was a tremendous part of my life, but not the only part. When it is balanced with the rest of my life it doesn't even begin to describe who I am.<br><br>

